  "market_context": "ES on the 15-minute chart near the New York session. Price had been trending lower with midnight open acting as resistance, then traded into an up-close candle near the 8:30 timing window.",
  "key_observation": "At 8:30 ES made an opposing run higher and then closed below the up-close candle, validating that candle as a bearish order block. The 9:30 open then produced a brief run higher before dropping to sweep lows and continue the downtrend.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified that at 8:30 ES made a run higher into an up-close candle.",
    "Observed price closing below that up-close candle, validating it as a bearish order block.",
    "Noted price retraced into the newly formed order block ahead of 9:30.",
    "At 9:30, observed a small run higher on the lower time frame as a manipulation before distribution.",
    "Watched price drop lower and sweep out the prior lows, confirming downside continuation.",
    "Stepped back to the 4-hour candle to confirm an open-low (no high yet) structure with midnight used as resistance, validating the bearish daily delivery."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price distributed lower after 9:30, sweeping prior lows and continuing the bearish move as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "The 8:30 timing window often forms a manipulation that validates an order block; 9:30 then delivers the distribution. Studying these specific session timings around opposing runs reveals the recurring institutional delivery pattern.",
